# Windows batch files must keep CRLF — cmd.exe's parser corrupts on LF-only
# scripts when commandlets like UnrealEditor-Cmd return through them
# (observed on UE 5.7: subsequent %VAR% expansions silently strip leading
# chars, cleanup section skipped). Kazzinc 5.4 happened to survive; 5.7
# does not.
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf
*.ps1 text eol=crlf
